# prose_translation = And it was already about mid-morning and the stage was near where he intended to halt, when Pateguas, a Persian man of Cyrus's faithful suite, appeared riding at full speed with his horse sweating, and immediately he began to shout to all whom he met, both in Persian and in Greek, that the King was approaching with a large army prepared for battle.
