# prose_translation = And when he was sent down by his father as Satrap of Lydia, Greater Phrygia, and Cappadocia, and was also appointed general of all who are required to muster in the plain of Castolus, he first of all showed himself to be of the highest importance that, if he made a treaty or an agreement or a promise to anyone, he should in no way prove false.
# literal_translation = When but he-was-sent-down by the father satrap of-Lydia both and Phrygia the great and Cappadocia, general but also of-all to-whom it-pertains into of-Castolus plain to-be-mustered, first on-the-one-hand he-showed himself, that about most he-would-make, if to-anyone he-had-made-truce and if to-anyone he-had-agreed and if to-anyone he-had-promised anything, nothing to-lie.
